{"title":"Manzanita Cycles 130 mm Travel Manifesto Hardtail","link":"https://theradavist.com/manzanita-cycles-130-mm-travel-manifesto-hardtail/","date":1747407181000,"content":"<p><em>Reno, Nevada-based <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/manzanita-cycles/\" target=\"_blank\">Manzanita Cycles</a> just announced its Manifesto hardtail model. Featuring 130 mm of travel and heaps of details. Let’s check it out…</em><span></span></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-3.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-3.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Manzanita Manifesto Quick Hits</h3>\n<ul>\n<li>$4,975 XT build</li>\n<li>$2,200 frame</li>\n<li>130 mm travel</li>\n<li>Made in Nevada</li>\n<li>29×2.6 tire clearance</li>\n<li>UDH / Sram Transmission</li>\n<li>Size-specific variable chainstay length</li>\n<li>External routing</li>\n<li>Six stock sizes</li>\n</ul>\n<p>The Manifesto is a 130 mm-travel, 29er hardtail made for maximum fun on the trail. The geometry is just the right amount of progressive, giving you confidence on the steeps while still feeling agile when it’s playtime. Maintenance is a breeze thanks to the externally routed lines secured with custom 3D-printed guides that provide protection where needed and a rattle-free ride.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-8.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-8.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-8.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Features</h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-5.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-5.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-5.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-10.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-10.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-10.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-10.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>These dropouts are compatible with SRAM’s Universal Derailleur Hanger, the new Transmission, and every other drivetrain on the market</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-7.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-7.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-7.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-7.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The offset bosses on the seat tube allow you to install a water bottle cage without interfering with your long dropper post.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-14.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-14.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-14.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-14.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The externally-routed lines make maintenance a breeze. A custom 3d-printed housing guide protects the frame and lines from damage.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-2.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-2.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita-Cycles-Manifesto-Hardtail-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita_Manifesto_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita_Manifesto_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita_Manifesto_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://media.theradavist.com/uploads/2025/05/Manzanita_Manifesto_Hardtail_Geo.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3>Geometry</h3>\n<p>Variable chainstay lengths with a consistent seat tube angle mean taller riders will feel more supported on the Manifesto and shorter riders will feel more agile while climbing.</p>\n<p>Check out more at <a href=\"https://manzanitacycles.com/bikes/manifesto/\" target=\"_blank\">Manzanita Cycles</a> and see more of Nick’s work in the Related archives below.</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/manzanita-cycles-130-mm-travel-manifesto-hardtail/\">Manzanita Cycles 130 mm Travel Manifesto Hardtail</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"21dcbff6a3879f01b0a1a8ffcd2c7b24fd1ce6bf69b298a085ea493d0ff4acd2","category":"Cycling"}